         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Fragment of a large leaf right behind the string hole, traces of vertical and horizontal ruling; on the verso side only the left part is covered with writing up until an ornamental vertical line, which is typical of the final leaf and colophon of a manuscript; does not belong with either of the 14A leaves.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">The supplementation <hi>päkre</hi> is not possible; an alternative reading could be <hi>p(·)äk(·)aṃ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment"><hi>(a)padāṃ</hi> = <hi>avadāna-</hi></note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">cf. the Skt. PN <hi>citradyuti-</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="lingcomment"><hi>ṣkaimpa</hi> is the Kom. of a fem. PN.</note></p>
